

Comcast Business is the division of the Comcast Corporation which handles the sales, marketing, and delivery of Comcast services such as Internet, phone, and Ethernet to small and medium businesses.1 In 2012, Comcast Business grew by 34.2%, the fastest growth of any of Comcast's products, amounting to $2.4 billion in revenue.234
Background
Comcast was founded in 1963 in Tupelo, Mississippi, and the Business Services division was added in 2006.5 By 2012, the Business Services division had the highest growth rate of any of Comcast's services.6 The division's revenue has increased every year since 2006, when the division's earnings were $265 million. As of 2012, the revenue of Comcast Business was $2.4 billion. Bill Stemper has overseen the expansion of Comcast Business, and in 2013, he was given a Vanguard Award from the National Cable &amp; Telecommunications Association.7
Metro Ethernet Forum Award
In November, 2013, Comcast Business was awarded Service Provider of the Year award by the Metro Ethernet Forum.8
